    {
        "content": "<p>What is the difference between let and def? For example I wanted in the whole file to have</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"n\">def</span> <span class=\"n\">B</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">set</span> <span class=\"n\">V</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"n\">closed_ball</span> <span class=\"mi\">0</span> <span class=\"mi\">1</span>\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>but then in a later proof I use</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"n\">intros</span> <span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"n\">hx</span><span class=\"o\">,</span>\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>while showing that B is contained in something but it doesn't work. However, if I use let it does work.</p>",
        "id": 180527738,
        "sender_full_name": "Lambert A'Campo",
        "timestamp": 1573572494
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Let and def are morally similar but live in different syntactic classes. As for your particular example we need more context, preferably a MWE</p>",
        "id": 180529194,
        "sender_full_name": "Mario Carneiro",
        "timestamp": 1573573322
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>What is a MWE?</p>",
        "id": 180532307,
        "sender_full_name": "Lambert A'Campo",
        "timestamp": 1573575061
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>minimal working example</p>",
        "id": 180532322,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1573575069
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ok so here is a not quite minimal example and I don't understand why the declaration of the example has type problems.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"kn\">variables</span>\n<span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">V</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">normed_group</span> <span class=\"n\">V</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">complete_space</span> <span class=\"n\">V</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">normed_space</span> <span class=\"n\">ℝ</span> <span class=\"n\">V</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">def</span> <span class=\"n\">B&#39;</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">set</span> <span class=\"n\">V</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"n\">closed_ball</span> <span class=\"mi\">0</span> <span class=\"mi\">1</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">B&#39;</span> <span class=\"err\">⊆</span> <span class=\"err\">⋃</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">V</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">H</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"err\">∈</span> <span class=\"n\">B&#39;</span><span class=\"o\">),</span> <span class=\"n\">ball</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">5</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"k\">begin</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">sorry</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">end</span>\n</pre></div>",
        "id": 180534130,
